Wolfblade::

She barked at him playfully and took off down the hall.  She didn't
let herself run at full speed or she'd outrun him.  She was grinning
wolfishly ear to ear as she trotted down the hall. 



--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, robert riley <bustercross365@y...> wrote:
> Malice:
>  
> He blinked a bit then grinned broadly.  He leapt of his stool to the
table tops and patted Celeron's shoulder as he passed by.
>  
> "Easy there.  Relax a bit," he said as he leapt to the final table
seperating him and Wolfblade.
>  
> He crouched on the table, thankful it was bolted down, as he perched
on the edge, his toes digging into the table a bit as he prepared to
lunge after Wolfblade.  His tail swayed a bit behind him, betraying
his enjoyment as he grinned down at her.  
>  
> 
> 
> Dark Mouse <raccoon7679@y...> wrote:
> Wolfblade::
> 
> She grinned at him and chuckled."Oh I dunno. Gin, Old Maidbot,
> Checkers, or how about...."  She threw the dart and watched it land
> within an inch of his hand. "I know, our old favorite."  She grinned
> seductively at him. "TAG!  Your it."  she transformed into wolf mode
> and dashed to the door.  She stopped at the doorway and faced him. 
> She tilted her wolf head sideways and gave him an anticipating look.
> 
> 
> 
> "HA!  Is that all you got?  You boasted such power, such skill! 
Where is your power and skill now?  You disappoint me, ha ha ha haa!"
